 18<br> <font color=#EFD68C>(1/17/03 4:55:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fslipstreambbs12353frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   On flaming</span><hr size=1> Having spent a considerable amount of time at a place where flaming is not only openly encouraged, it's an art form, I feel I have some qualification to give my OPINION (note that word opinion) on flaming.  You will probably see two kinds of flames, the &quot;RP, I was just kidding&quot; kind, and the kind where someone really does get angry.  In the first instance, it might be nice to keep them all confined to one forum, with some sort of code in the thread title to let people know there will be insults, flames and rough language and they enter at their own risk.  A suggestion would be  &quot;(F) Thread Title (F) &quot;...where (F)= flame.<br>
<br>
You don't want flames all over the board.  If Slipstreamers were comfortable with that, the TK membership would have trippled overnight.<br>
<br>
The other kind of flame...where someone gets angry will be a little more complicated.  Message boards have a very warped sense of time passing.  Sometimes things happen almost real time, and in other cases, people may not see a message that triggers a response until hours or days later.  People will get angry and tempers will flare and it has always been my opinion that you give people a chance to correct (edit) flames they posted in anger and offer an apology before any kind of warnings are given.  Everyone is an adult...or adult enough to know how to work things out without a babysitter (moderator)<br>
<br>
Thats not to belittle moderators.  But anyone who has experienced overly moderated or unfairly moderated boards will probably be tempted to take moderating duties here very seriously and feel they have to be the police of their forums.<br>
<br>
If you start out with a policy of warnings and bans systems, that means you are expecting behavior that will result in warnings and bans and if you are expecing it, the moderators will find it.<br>
<br>
Asking nicely, showing respect and being able to admit mistakes ( oooohhhh who do we know that never admits to mistakes??) will go over a lot better than warnings and bans.<br>
<br>
is this place no smoking yet?<br>
<br>
