I think it would be nice just to keep the RP threads completely off limits to flames.  Any flames would after all be in character...  No need for the (F) in the title.<br>
<br>
Now Misc roleplaying threads could add that in so that everyone understands.  Smite wars and the like should automatically be considered places where some off color flames might take place at a moment's notice.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Alot has to do with intent and damage done. <br>
<br>
My feelings on a warning ban system is that it's unnecessary.<br>
<br>
Friendly warnings, reminders and things will be around, of course, but as far as counting toward some magical number that will get you banned...  I hope it doesn't come out that way.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Bans should be reserved for the true deviants, like porn spammers and the like.<br>
<br>
I like the idea of asking people to edit and apologize.<br>
<br>
If they refuse, then we edit it for them if it's necessary.  Mild flames aren't too much of a worry really, it's the full on assaults that fall into this category. <p>  &quot;To build may have to be the slow and laborious task of years. To destroy can be the thoughtless act of a single day.&quot; <br>
